<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15674">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b
        >NOTE: Prohibited Activities <br />The Scouting America's
        <em>Guide to Safe Scouting</em> states under "Prohibited Activities"
        that flying in aircraft as part of a search and rescue mission is a
        prohibited activity for youth members. For complete information, see
        Scouting America's
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/gss/"
          target="_blank"
          ><i>Guide to Safe Scouting.</i></a
        ></b
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15675">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Search%20and%20Rescue.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15676">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      <b>Hazards and First Aid.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15676 mb-requirement-id-15677">
        (a) Show or explain first aid for, and prevention of, injuries and
        conditions that searchers and subjects could develop during an SAR
        situation, including:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15677 mb-requirement-id-15715">
        (1) Dehydration <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/KahsIEbFROI" target="_blank"
          >Dehydration (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15677 mb-requirement-id-15716">
        (2) Heatstroke <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/8gn3DEYOPuE" target="_blank"
          >Heat Exhaustion vs Heat Stroke (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/PpHM4DfPZQU" target="_blank"
          >Heat Stroke (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15677 mb-requirement-id-15717">
        (3) Hypothermia <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/my6JB41apTw" target="_blank"
          >Hypothermia (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15677 mb-requirement-id-15718">
        (4) Shock <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/S0aCHtEn7to" target="_blank"
          >Recognizing and Treating Shock (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/AHls9NRGCZk" target="_blank">Shock (video)</a>
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15677 mb-requirement-id-15719">
        (5) Blisters <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/5y2QIZwzfuI" target="_blank"
          >Blisters (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15677 mb-requirement-id-15720">
        (6) Eye injuries <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/zULuu4QwX4s" target="_blank"
          >First Aid for Eyes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15677 mb-requirement-id-15721">
        (7) Ankle and knee sprains <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Z_kCbkxR4xk" target="_blank"
          >Figure 8 Ankle Wrap (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/safety-moments/orthopedic-injuries/"
          target="_blank"
          >Orthopedic Injuries (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/BAUiP1P3GE0" target="_blank"
          >Bone, Joint, and Muscle Injuries (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15677 mb-requirement-id-15722">
        (8) Bug bites of chiggers, ticks, mosquitoes, and biting gnats <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/mwAHhOwqeX4" target="_blank"
          >Tick Checks (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/m4iapNcv8-Q" target="_blank"
          >Mosquito Bites (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15677 mb-requirement-id-15723">
        (9) Bee stings <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/01Po5RTNfhs" target="_blank"
          >Bee Stings (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/nv2BUxZMWAI" target="_blank"
          >Treatment of a Bee Sting (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15677 mb-requirement-id-15724">
        (10) Bites of spiders <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/QQVYRvD55Uc" target="_blank"
          >What You Need To Know About Spider Bites (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15677 mb-requirement-id-15725">
        (11) Sting of a scorpion <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YFI2VMy6mT0" target="_blank"
          >Scorpion Stings (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15677 mb-requirement-id-15726">
        (12) Bite of a wild mammal <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/X0HYjzU2NKk" target="_blank"
          >Treatment of Animal Bites (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15677 mb-requirement-id-15727">
        (13) Bite of a venomous snake <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_H8ROJD1oIo" target="_blank"
          >Snakebites (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/PZ93mhPZS3s" target="_blank"
          >Rattlesnake Bites (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15676 mb-requirement-id-15678">
        (b) Explain how the Scout Basic Essentials address hazards outdoors and
        help lost Scouts stay safe before they are rescued. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://scoutlife.org/outdoors/outdoorarticles/6976/scout-outdoor-essentials-checklist/"
          target="_blank"
          >Scout Outdoor Essentials (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Search%20and%20Rescue/Scout%20Essentials%20and%20Outdoor%20Hazards.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Scout Essentials and Outdoor Hazards (PDF)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YGQG0C0HBGw" target="_blank"
          >Essentials for Safe Hiking (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15676 mb-requirement-id-15728">
        (c) Discuss how the safety gear carried by SAR team members in their
        field packs address SAR hazards. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/8G2pYjxCfgg" target="_blank"
          >What I Carry in My Search and Rescue Pack (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15679">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      <b>Staying and Getting Found.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15679 mb-requirement-id-15680">
        (a) Explain how a trip plan and the buddy system help Scouts with
        staying found and getting found. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/79WYqkiExZU" target="_blank"
          >How To Plan an Adventure (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://scoutingmagazine.org/2007/03/outdoor-smarts-lost-and-found/"
          target="_blank"
          >Scout Trip Planning (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.adventurealan.com/why-you-should-make-a-trip-plan/"
          target="_blank"
          >Why You Should Make Trip Plans (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15679 mb-requirement-id-15681">
        (b) Explain how seasonal and daily weather changes affect Trip Plans.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/CLQo5ftVqnc" target="_blank"
          >Search and Rescue Expert Stresses Importance of Preparedness
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15679 mb-requirement-id-15682">
        (c) Explain and show how a lost Scout could send signals that would
        alert a ground, airborne, or water SAR team to their location. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/Srj6Cy6D0YU" target="_blank"
          >5 Ground To Air Signals That Save Lives (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/6ZDiIfqTI-k" target="_blank"
          >Various Ways To Signal for Search and Rescue (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://scoutingmagazine.org/2019/02/signaling-for-help-in-the-wilderness/"
          target="_blank"
          >Signaling for Help in the Wilderness (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15679 mb-requirement-id-15729">
        (d) Demonstrate how to use a signaling mirror. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/kYN46GuZmpE" target="_blank"
          >How To Use a Signal Mirror (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://scoutingmagazine.org/issues/0103/d-outs.html"
          target="_blank"
          >The Signal Mirror: A Low-Tech Lifesaver (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15679 mb-requirement-id-15730">
        (e) Explain how a Personal Locator Beacon (PLB) works and the role of
        the Air Force Rescue Coordination Center (AFRCC). <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/xwbgU9envik" target="_blank"
          >How Does an EPIRB Work? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YM4V76rTMtI" target="_blank"
          >How Modern Rescue Beacons Work—The Anatomy of a Rescue | EPIRB and
          Personal Locator Beacons (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.sarsat.noaa.gov/emergency-406-beacons/"
          target="_blank"
          >Emergency Beacons (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15683">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      <b>Maps.</b> Using a map, a compass and a GPS device or app approved by
      your counselor, do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15683 mb-requirement-id-15693">
        (a) Point out and explain the 5 D's (Date, Description, Details,
        Direction or Declination, Distance) of the map. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/0zbCEXj_29U" target="_blank"
          >The 5 D's in Navigation (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://mountaintrails.ie/blog/using-the-five-ds-in-a-navigation-strategy/"
          target="_blank"
          >The Five D's in Map Navigation (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15683 mb-requirement-id-15694">
        (b) Choose a location on the map and record the altitude, latitude,
        longitude, and US National Grid coordinates. Describe how these
        coordinate systems differ. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.fgdc.gov/usng/how-to-read-usng/index_html"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Read a US National Grid Map (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Tm-k5d3Ar54" target="_blank"
          >Work With a Grid in ArcGIS Pro (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15683 mb-requirement-id-15684">
        (c) Orient the map and take a bearing to another map location. Estimate
        the distance between, and describe the terrain between, the two
        locations. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://troopleader.scouting.org/rank-advancement-skills/campcraft/navigation-and-measurements/"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Use a Map and Compass (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15683 mb-requirement-id-15731">
        (d) Show a hypothetical place last seen and point out an area on your
        map that could be used for containment using natural or human-made
        boundaries. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/-fbXrnZ0C3o" target="_blank"
          >Search Containment (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15713">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      <b>Incident Command System (ICS).</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15713 mb-requirement-id-15732">
        (a) Explain how a local ICS is organized and how it compares with
        Scouting's patrol method. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/P-dPBso2xPM" target="_blank"
          >Introduction to ICS (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.cfsph.iastate.edu/Emergency-Response/Just-in-Time/01-Incident-Command-System-Overview-HANDOUT.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Incident Command Structure (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15713 mb-requirement-id-15733">
        (b) Explain how local community agencies work to train for and manage
        search and rescue situations. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/h1B9mwnmEaQ" target="_blank"
          >Search &amp; Rescue Training (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/A-SiF8cdO9k" target="_blank"
          >CERT Search &amp; Rescue Training (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ZwClCJ-0n-U" target="_blank"
          >What It Takes To Be on a Search and Rescue Team (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15714">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      <b>SAR Teams.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15714 mb-requirement-id-15734">
        (a) Explain the official duties of a search and rescue team. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ZF5m_fge5cY" target="_blank"
          >What You Should Know As A Search &amp; Rescue Team Member (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15714 mb-requirement-id-15735">
        (b) Explain the differences between wilderness, urban, and water SARs.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://sregear.com/blogs/news/the-different-types-of-search-and-rescue"
          target="_blank"
          >Types of Search and Rescue (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15714 mb-requirement-id-15736">
        (c) Identify four types of search and rescue teams and explain
        situations where they are used. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.focuspointintl.com/trending/disaster-assistance/understanding-the-different-types-of-search-and-rescue-operations/"
          target="_blank"
          >Types of SAR Teams (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15695">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      <b>Search and Rescue Procedures.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15695 mb-requirement-id-15696">
        (a) Explain the difference between search and rescue. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/zanbVmtx4dw" target="_blank"
          >Search or Rescue (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.kyem.ky.gov/home/showpublisheddocument/1370/638864015872401722"
          target="_blank"
          >Search Methods (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15695 mb-requirement-id-15697">
        (b) Explain the difference between PLS (place last seen) and LKP (last
        known point) <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="http://www.sarmath.com/terms/initial-planning-point"
          target="_blank"
          >PLS and LKP (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15695 mb-requirement-id-15698">
        (c) Explain the importance of effective communication in SAR operations.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YE-WG9_IWTc" target="_blank"
          >Urban Search and Rescue Communications Specialist Training (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15695 mb-requirement-id-15737">
        (d) Explain how predictions of "lost person behavior" determine SAR
        search plans for a young child, a teenager, and an adult. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/e2x38A4aAoU" target="_blank"
          >Lost Person Behavior Scenario (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/NUgeL0R_qZU" target="_blank"
          >Help Us Find You (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15695 mb-requirement-id-15738">
        (e) Explain the following terms: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://myem.jibc.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/SAR-Glossary-from-SAR-Mgmt-Course.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Search and Rescue Glossary (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15738 mb-requirement-id-15739">
        (1) Evaluating search urgency <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.criminaljustice.ny.gov/missing/docs/search-urgency-chart.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Urban Search Urgency Evaluation Form (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15738 mb-requirement-id-15740">
        (2) Establishing confinement <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/JxWP2D538PY" target="_blank"
          >Establishing Confinement (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15738 mb-requirement-id-15741">
        (3) Scent item
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15738 mb-requirement-id-15742">
        (4) Area air scent dog <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/2HFOg1LRFmc" target="_blank"
          >Training For A Search And Rescue (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.buckeyesardogs.org/scent/" target="_blank"
          >Scent and Rescue Dogs (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15738 mb-requirement-id-15743">
        (5) Briefing and debriefing <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://markaray.wordpress.com/2016/05/17/thorns-and-roses-and-plcs/"
          target="_blank"
          >Thorns and Roses (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/S__cfVygihk" target="_blank"
          >Start, Stop, Continue (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15738 mb-requirement-id-15744">
        (6) Clue awareness <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/luSyvsEcXzs" target="_blank"
          >Clue Awareness (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://rescue101sar.org/blog/f/tracking-the-essential-skill-for-search-and-rescue-teams"
          target="_blank"
          >Tracking in SAR (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://aa3sd.net/newsar/sar_ftm_v1_0_0/presentations/pdf/9_clue_detection.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Clue Awareness and Detection (PPT)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15738 mb-requirement-id-15745">
        (7) Evidence preservation <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/ao70uTz9N24" target="_blank"
          >Evidence Search (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15738 mb-requirement-id-15746">
        (8) Tracking a subject <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/CBYg9TZMvZA" target="_blank"
          >Footprint Tracking (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/bFVckg9ra7o" target="_blank"
          >Dog Scent Tracking Demo (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/uNIbbUt-KCY" target="_blank"
          >Tracking With Drones (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/0GRsfcVZK_A" target="_blank"
          >Human Tracking, Whistle Science @ 8:30 (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/yAf0UM-nglk" target="_blank"
          >Tracking Dog Scent-Preservation (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15738 mb-requirement-id-15747">
        (9) Locating a subject using attraction <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.cibolasar.org/?page_id=478" target="_blank"
          >Ground Search Techniques (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15738 mb-requirement-id-15748">
        (10) Hasty search <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/3_ELcOAH1Iw" target="_blank"
          >Hasty Searching (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/Mw6V0W4Vyk0" target="_blank"
          >Search Types (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15738 mb-requirement-id-15749">
        (11) Trail sweep search <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://franklinsar.blogspot.com/2015/12/conducting-sound-sweep-for-search.html"
          target="_blank"
          >Conducting a Sound Sweep (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15738 mb-requirement-id-15750">
        (12) Grid search <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/Mw6V0W4Vyk0" target="_blank"
          >Zone Search (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15699">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      <b>Plan and Complete a Search.</b> Do the following with a team of Scouts,
      friends, or family to execute a practice SAR exercise:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15699 mb-requirement-id-15700">
        (a) Choose a hypothetical SAR scenario, either one presented in the
        <i>Search and Rescue</i> merit badge pamphlet or one approved by your
        counselor. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.countyofglenn.net/government/departments/sheriff/search-rescue/training-response-activities"
          target="_blank"
          >Training Scenarios (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Search%20and%20Rescue/Lost%20Scout%20Scenario.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Lost Scout Scenario (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15699 mb-requirement-id-15701">
        (b) Develop an Incident Action Plan (IAP) for a hasty search using the
        scenario information. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.sarbc.org/sarbc/pdfs/SearchMgmtActionPlan.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Developing an IAP (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15699 mb-requirement-id-15702">
        (c) Before the search begins, conduct a PAUSE briefing to review
        hazards, safety concerns, personal and shared Scout Basic Essentials,
        and other gear. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/rDSeEBuCyVI" target="_blank"
          >Pause. Look. Act. (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/FL5jTZJv5Ts" target="_blank"
          >Risk Assessment (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/healthsafety/pdf/680-046.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >PAUSE Safety Moment (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15699 mb-requirement-id-15703">
        (d) Execute the search.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15699 mb-requirement-id-15751">
        (e) After the search, hold a team debriefing to discuss the search,
        problems, successful and unsuccessful tactics, and ideas for
        improvement. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://markaray.wordpress.com/2016/05/17/thorns-and-roses-and-plcs/"
          target="_blank"
          >Philmont Thorns and Roses (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15704">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      <b>Careers.</b> Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15704 mb-requirement-id-15705">
        (a) Explore careers related to Search and Rescue merit badge or
        emergency management. Research one career to learn about the training
        and education needed, costs, job prospects, salary, job duties, and
        career advancement. With permission of your parent or guardian, your
        research methods may include an internet or library search, an interview
        with a professional in the field, or a visit to a location where people
        in this career work. Discuss with your counselor both your findings and
        what about this profession might make it an interesting career. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qKA27Zpw8o4" target="_blank"
          >What it Means to be a Search and Rescue Responder (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/lowz7P4QIVs" target="_blank"
          >What It Actually Takes To Be a Rescue Swimmer in the Coast Guard
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/yY2kdlk4zps" target="_blank"
          >U.S. Air Force: Combat Search and Rescue (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/uRmE4z1sGbA" target="_blank"
          >Emergency Management Directors (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15704 mb-requirement-id-15706">
        (b) Explore how you could use knowledge and skills from this merit badge
        to serve as a volunteer on a disaster relief team, a wilderness rescue
        team, or a ski patrol. Research any training needed, expenses, and
        organizations that promote or support it. Discuss with your counselor
        what short-term and long-term goals you might have if you pursue this.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/wpC861dIwvQ" target="_blank"
          >How To Prepare To Join a Search and Rescue Team | SAR Training for
          Finding Missing Persons (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/FfBXzSF__90" target="_blank"
          >Volunteer Search and Rescue Teams (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ZwClCJ-0n-U" target="_blank"
          >Search and Rescue Volunteers (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
